1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 d5 3. e3
{ The proper way to get to the Colle system. White refrains from playing c4 and develops his minor pieces first. There are usually two setups White opts for:  1.@@EndBracket@@ Bd3/O-O/c3/Nbd2 and fight for e4.   2.@@EndBracket@@ Bd3/O-O/b3/Bb2/Nbd2 and fight for e4. }
3... c5 { We stick to our fixed move order of Nf6-d5-c5 and grab the center. }
4. b3 cxd4
{ The right time to take on d4. The white bishop will now look stupid on b2, with their own pawn blocking the d4-square. If the bishop develops on the other diagonal @@StartBracket@@f4/g5@@EndBracket@@ the c3 square becomes a target. }
5. exd4 Nc6
{ Black intends to bring the light-squared bishop out and play e6. The engines already prefer Black. A detailed explanation and analysis are given in the main file. }
