{ A typical move that we have been seeing for a long time. Black is reluctant to give away the center. }
9. f4
{ Still trying to create a mess on the center by constantly attacking it.  9.e3  has been played a few times, but after  9...Bg4  10.f3  Be6  Black gets a clear advantage due to the domination in the center. }
9... e4
{ Many other moves were giving advantage to Black and the engine had different ways to claim an advantage. However, this is a no-brainer move that is easy to play. There was nothing wrong with the pawn sacrifice  9...Be7  that the engine also likes. However, after this move, Black keeps the center and, I don't see any obvious compensation for White. }
