{ It is obvious that White cannot create an attack on the center, and Black will play Bg7-O-O shortly.   @@StartBracket@@More importantly, White will also have to deal with Rc8 ideas that gain a tempo against White's queen. This position occurred in a few correspondence games, and Black never lost a single one and won one game. That also underlines the solidity of Black's position. }
