3... c5 4. c3
{ After  4.dxc5  e6  Black gets the pawn on c5, as  5.b4  a5  6.a3  runs into  6...axb4  7.axb4  b6  . It doesn't make sense to lock the c1 bishop and give the center to Black then fight for equality. I don't see this coming ever from any strong player. }
