{ This position can come from Caro Kann @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.e4  c6  2.d4  d5  3.exd5  cxd5  4.c4  Nf6  . Here more than 40000 games are played with  5.Nc3  and about only 1000 games played with  5.Nf3  , which is our current position. It shows White tries to avoid this position in Caro Kann. The main disadvantage of having Nf3 instead of Nc3 is that White is not putting enough pressure on the d5 pawn quickly. Thus, Black is not obliged to play e6. We have plenty of choices here to get a comfortable position. }
