[White "Queen's Gambit Declined: Overview"]
[Black "3) Queen's Gambit Declined: Overview "]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5
{ The Queens Gambit Declined is especially effective when White has committed his knight to f3. This way, White never gets the dangerous Bd3-Ne2 setup.   The major moves in this position are:  -  4.Nc3  when we opt for Semi-Tarrasch with  4...c5  .   -  4.g3  getting into a Catalan System.   These two lines are covered in various chapters with separate overviews. Right now, we will focus on all other moves apart from  4.Nc3  and  4.g3  . }
4. cxd5
{ This is the best example where the knight on f3 is misplaced. White's best setup in Exchange QGD is to get Bd3-Ne2-O-O-f3 ideas. With already committed Nf3, White is missing this formation. }
4... exd5 5. Nc3 { The most popular move in the position. } 5... c6
{ It is the ideal pawn formation. This position can also come from Semi-Slav @@StartBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/ppp2ppp/4pn2/3p4/2PP4/5N2/PP2PPPP/RNBQKB1R w KQkq - 0 4@@EndFEN@@  4.Nc3  c6  @@EndBracket@@, where taking on d5 is not the main or critical move. }
6. Qc2
{ White plays against the bishop on c8 and takes away its best square on f5. }
6... Bd6
{ This variation got popular recently. In 2021 it was played by Anish and Ding. Black ignores White's Bg5 ideas. }
7. Bg5
{ White is silently threatening  7...--  8.Bxf6  Qxf6  9.Nxd5  when the bishop on c8 hangs. }
7... O-O
{ Statistics: 90+ games, Black played  7...h6  , which immediately loses after  8.Bxf6  Qxf6  9.Nxd5  as the c8 bishop hangs. In 60+ games, White automatically played  9.Bh4  . This is what happens when one memorizes moves without understanding the reasoning behind them :@@EndBracket@@ }
8. e3 h6 9. Bh4 Be6 { Getting ready to play Nbd7 next. } 10. Bd3 Nbd7
{ White's main problem is the misplaced knight on f3. The key idea in this line is to have a knight on e2 with f3-e4 ideas. Both Anish and Ding had no problem from the Black side. More details and plans are explained clearly in the main file. Black should make sure White doesn't get b4-b5 ideas, so a timely a5 will be essential. }
*

