4. c5 { White tries to shut down Black's bishop and tries to gain more space. }
4... b6
{ Naturally, we don't want to allow that, so we strike back immediately. } 5.
b4
{ The only way to justify their previous move. Although it would have been wiser to give up the center by playing  5.cxb6  , but after  5...axb6  , Black would eventually play c5 and gain more control over the center. }
5... a5
{ White's rook on a1 is not protected. Thus they can't hold on to the b4-c5 pawn. Black takes over now. }
