1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. e3
{ This way, White temporarily stops Black from playing c5. Although Black can still play  5...c5  after  6.cxd5  Nxd5  7.e4  , they will be slightly worse as Nxc3 is not available anymore. }
4... Be7
{ Black keeps the c5 idea in hand and first goes for a quick short castle. } 5.
b3
{ White will eventually make the moves Bd3-O-O-Bb2, and it can happen in a lot of permutations and combinations, which will definitely involve a lot of transpositions.   Essentially the main difference is the choice for White whether to put the b1 knight on c3 or d2. In order to avoid confusion, I kept all the lines under the 6.Bd3-O-O-Bb2 move order and only at this point gave the option of Nbd2/Nc3.   White could also start with  5.Nbd2  O-O  6.b3  , and after  6...c5  , we will eventually reach a position that is covered via 5.b3-Bd3-O-O-Bb2 move order. }
5... O-O
{ White can choose any move order, but we will get to a similar setup irrespective of which move order White opts for. }
6. Nc3
{ Another different move order. White is now committed to Nc3 and loses the option of Nbd2. In any case, Black's play remains fixed. Strike with c5. }
6... c5 7. dxc5
{ The only independent move.  7.Bd3  cxd4  8.exd4  b6  9.Bb2  or  9.O-O  Bb7  10.Bb2  transposes back to our 6.Bd3 line.   The same is applicable for  7.Bb2  cxd4  8.exd4  b6  9.Bd3  Bb7  10.O-O  that get us back to our 6.Bd3 line.   White could play  7.cxd5  but after  7...cxd4  8.Nxd4  Nxd5  Black has no problems in the position with the white king still stuck in the center. }
7... dxc4 8. Bxc4
{ After  8.Qxd8  Rxd8  9.Bxc4  Bxc5  Black gets a balanced endgame with Nc6-b6-Bb7-Rac8 coming next. }
8... Qxd1+ 9. Kxd1 { White wants to keep the king in the center. } 9... Nbd7
{ Planning to take on c5 with the knight. } 10. Na4 Ne4 11. Ke2 Ndxc5
{ Black gets his knight on c5. He will soon play Rd8-b6-Bb7. There is no weakness in the position, and Black has a nice endgame to look forward to. ½-½ Marks Robert @@StartBracket@@2363@@EndBracket@@ - Cunningham Peter J @@StartBracket@@2163@@EndBracket@@ ICCF 2021 }
