6... cxd4 7. O-O
{ White will have to include this move first before taking the pawn to avoid Qa5+. }
7... Nc6
{ This move was introduced in FIDE Grand Swiss 2019 by SL Narayanan,  who played it against Dubov. It was also played twice @@StartBracket@@#1 #2@@EndBracket@@ by GM Ter Sahakyan later. This move is much stronger than  7...Be7  , which Hikaru played against Magnus in an online rapid. }
8. e5 { We must always check this move. } 8... h6 9. Bh4 g5
{ The standard way of unpinning the knight. } 10. Bg3
{ White could not take on g5 as the e5 pawn would be hanging at the end of the variation. }
10... Ne4
{ Black gets the double bishop and remains a pawn up for now. The pawn on e5 will also become a target once Black gets the bishop to g7. }
