{ This move was introduced in FIDE Grand Swiss 2019 by SL Narayanan,  who played it against Dubov. It was also played twice @@StartBracket@@#1 #2@@EndBracket@@ by GM Ter Sahakyan later. This move is much stronger than  7...Be7  , which Hikaru played against Magnus in an online rapid. }
8. Re1 h6
{ I like this move which is an improvement over the Dubov, D @@StartBracket@@2699@@EndBracket@@-Sunilduth Lyna, N @@StartBracket@@2611@@EndBracket@@ Douglas 2019 game. }
9. Bh4
{ It is important that after  9.Bxf6  Black takes  9...gxf6  . This stops any kind of e5 ideas.  Black gets to keep the extra pawn, the bishop pair, and occupies the half-open g-file.  Black remains better there. }
9... e5
{ Once the bishop is out on h4, Black closes the center and consolidates the pawn on d4. }
10. Qb3
{ After  10.Bd5  Bb4  11.Nbd2  Bg4  with the double pin White still struggles to get back the pawn, and Black gets a comfortable position. }
10... Qe7 11. Nbd2 g5
{ A very important resource. Black shuts the bishop on h4 just in time and consolidates the center. }
12. Bg3 Nd7
{ With Bg7-O-O coming next, it would be difficult for White to prove sufficient compensation for the pawn. }
