{ The main option. Earlier, White tried to play less ambitiously without taking on d5, which still remains popular among all levels. }
5... Nxd5
{ This is the proper Semi-Tarrasch. Unlike the regular Tarrasch, in the Semi-Tarrasch Defense, Black does not accept an isolated pawn. This move has been played frequently by Kramnik, Ding, and Magnus, among many other top GMs who frequently employ this variation. The solidity of this line is beyond any doubt, but often people do not realize how sharp and dynamic it can get. No wonder many young players like Abdusattarov, Keymer, etc. picked up this line and played it regularly. }
6. e3
{ White is now ready for the  6...Nxc3  7.bxc3  cxd4  8.cxd4  Bb4+  9.Bd2  line when after the bishop trade the light-squared bishop becomes powerful and the center remains solid. }
6... Nc6
{ Black is not obliged to take on d4, and now plays against the dark-squared bishop on c1. }
7. Bd3
{ The main move in the position. White puts the bishop on the correct diagonal anticipating cxd4-exd4 positions. However, Black is not obliged to take on d4 now since there is no pressure on d5. }
7... Be7
{ Black can opt for cxd4-exd4 ideas, b6-Bb7 ideas, or take on c3 and play against the c3 pawn. A lot depends on how White chooses their setup. For now, Black just waits and castles quickly. We are now playing against the bishop on c1. }
8. O-O O-O 9. a3
{ White keeps waiting and gets ready for Qc2 ideas when Black wont have Nb4. }
9... cxd4
{ It was definitely possible to play  9...b6  , and it would be consistent with a similar plan of  9.Re1  lines. However, White can always start with 8.a3 and force Black to take on d4. }
10. exd4 Bf6 { Black wants to get Nce7-Bd7-Bc6 setup and remains very solid. }
11. Bc2
{ The most popular move is  11.Be4  , but after  11...Nce7  Black has nothing to worry about, and gets an excellent grip in the center. }
11... Nce7 12. Qd3 Ng6
{ This was played by Anish in the World Rapid 2021, and Black had an excellent position, enjoying total control while White had to suffer from his isolated pawn. }
