{ Admitting the mistake with  8.Bd2  doesn't give equality as Black then takes  8...dxc4  with a better position.   Playing  8.a3  Bxc3  9.bxc3  also remains tough for White since it is not clear how he will get back the pawn and repair the pawn structure. }
