[Black "Semi-Tarrasch - Sidelines  5.cxd5 Nxd5 6.Nxd5"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 c5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. Nxd5
{ This move is equally dubious and toothless as  6.dxc5  as Black gets to a pleasant endgame after  6...Nxc3  7.Qxd8  Kxd8  8.bxc3  Bxc5  and White ends up with a weak pawn on c3. }
6... Qxd5
{ Usually, the queen on d5 is not ideal. But without the knight getting to c3, who is going to get rid of this powerful queen? }
7. g3
{ White brings the bishop to harass the queen.  7.e3  Nc6  is covered from 5.e3 move order in a different file. }
7... Nc6
{ Black is on time to put pressure in the center before White can get rid of the queen. }
8. Bg2
{ 8.dxc5  Qxd1  9.Kxd1  Bxc5  is no fun for White as the king on d1 will have trouble finding a good place. }
8... cxd4 9. O-O e5
{ Just on time, Black managed to consolidate the center.  10.e3  can be answered with  10...Bg4  , pinning the knight. Black remains one pawn up for now. White will keep some compensation and hope that it brings them equality. }
*

[Event "?"]
