11. Ne5
{ This move was once played by a GM. But it just loses a pawn, and White must fight for equality. }
11... Nxc3
{ Against GM Hamdouchi,  Black wrongly decided not to accept the pawn sacrifice and opted for  11...h6  . }
12. bxc3 Bxe5
{ Black will take the pawn and make sure they gain a tempo by putting the knight to e5. }
13. dxe5 Qxd1 14. Rxd1 Nxe5
{ Black remains one pawn up. White definitely has compensation and will get an easy draw by reaching into some opposite color bishop endgames, but this does not bother Black. }
