[White "Chapter 10: Semi-Tarrasch (5.e3 Nc6 6.cxd5 Nxd5 7.Bc4)"]
[Black "Semi-Tarrasch - Sidelines: 5.e3 Nc6 6.cxd5 Nxd5 7.Bc4 #9"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 c5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. e3 Nc6 7. Bc4
{ One of the most common moves in this position. White builds pressure on the knight on d5. }
7... cxd4
{ Black plays thematically. White will now have to deal with the isolated pawn. Black now gets a strategic advantage while White fights for a dynamic advantage. }
