12... h6
{ It would take White a lot of time to switch the placement of the light-squared bishop and queen, and by that time, Black will get ample counterattacking chances. }
13. Qe2
{ Trying to reverse the queen and bishop position. This move was played once but looks too good to be true. One cannot attack by wasting so many tempos. }
13... Bd7 14. Bb1 Bc6
{ Now Black has completely taken over while White is just playing for one single idea. }
15. Qd3 Ng6
{ White's one and only idea of mating on h7 is gone and is now left with poor development and a worse pawn structure. }
