[FEN "rn3rk1/pb3ppp/1p2p3/8/3PP3/3B1N2/P4PPP/R4RK1 w - - 0 10"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ Exchanging Queens is one of the worst trades that White can do. Now White must be precise not to get into an annoying position. The central pawn becomes an obligation to defend, while Black's queenside pawns are an asset and are well protected. }
10. Rac1 Nc6 11. Rfd1 Rfd8 12. Bb1
{ White is busy defending the pawns in the center, and Black keeps bringing the pieces in the game with tempos. }
12... Rac8 { Threatening Nxd4. } 13. Kf1 Nxd4
{ Simplifying the game. It is also possible to play Kf8 and keep a dynamically balanced game. }
14. Nxd4 { Now it gets forcing for a while. } 14... Rxc1 15. Rxc1 Rxd4 16. Rc7
Rd1+ 17. Ke2 Rxb1 18. Rxb7 g5 { Fizzles out to a draw. } *

