{ We will see various rook moves in this file. In the introduction, the reasoning behind the rook moves is already explained. White waits for Black to commit with the b6/Nc6 plan before deciding on where to develop the light-squared bishop. }
11. Rc1
{ Waiting for Black to play b6 and then aiming to play Bd3 when Black won't have Nc6 ideas. }
11... b6
{ I have also tried  11...Nc6  , but I like this move more which goes as per our strategy of attacking the pawn on e4. }
12. Bd3
{ This is the whole point of starting with 11.Rc1. Black is missing Nc6 ideas. }
12... Bb7
{ Black admits that they can't play Nc6 and opts for the Bb7 plan. Black's argument is the combination of Bd3-Rc1 doesn't go together. The rook on c1 is never ideally placed as Black is generally happy to trade rooks. The bishop on d3 hinders the thematic d5 breaks. It sometimes helps White play on the queenside with a4-a5, but then the rook is needed on a1. }
13. O-O { White continues in the same path. } 13... Nd7
{ White has multiple options at this point. They can try to play on the kingside with h4 ideas, they can try on the queenside with a4 ideas, they could start kingside/center plans with Qe3/Qf4, or could develop the rook in the center first.   In any case, Black is not the slightest worried at this point. The main two moves in this position are  14.Qe3  and  14.Qf4  . }
14. Rfe1
{ This move was played only twice so far, but one of them was by Karpov in 2018.  14.Rfd1  doesn't fit in with the bishop on d3 as there is no threat of d5. In fact, after  14...Rc8  , the engine wants to play Ra1 admitting the inaccurate play earlier. }
14... Rc8 { Simple plan of exchanging more pieces. } 15. h3
{ A non-committal useful move by Karpov. } 15... Rxc1
{ In the above-mentioned game, Black played  15...Qe7  , but the text move is more to the point with our strategy of trading pieces. }
16. Rxc1 Qb8
{ Black will keep on trading pieces on the c-file. If the White rook leaves the c-file, the Black queen comes to the c-file and enters from c3. We already know from the introduction files that any endgames are fine for Black. }
