h6
{ Anticipating e5, Black takes measures against Ng5 ideas in the future.  14...Nf6  is also doable, but after  15.d5  exd5  16.e5  Ne4  17.Nd4  , we get a typical position where White gets compensation for a pawn, and practically it could be easier to play from the White side despite the computer evaluation of 0.00.   The standard  14...Rc8  would be easier to remember, but after  15.Rxc8  Qxc8  16.Rc1  Black is missing Qb8 ideas and needs to play differently. For now, Black takes precautions against e5 and plays the super useful move h6. }
15. h4
{ With the queen on f4, White gets ambitious with their kingside project and wants to play g4-g5 next. The move  15.h3  was also played a few times. It is toothless, and Black's play will remain identical as after  15.h4  lines. }
