16. Rxc8
{ 16.Rcd1  was played by L'Ami once in 2017. Black had the strong move  16...Rc3  with a positional threat of Rxd3-Ba6, exchanging a few more pieces. White could play  17.Rfe1  , but after  17...Qc7  , the queen on f4, will have to move back while Black gets domination on the queenside. }
16... Qxc8 17. Rc1 Qb8
{ The exact same position that we could reach without the inclusion of h6-h4 but decided against it. Black now wants to trade queens. }
