20. Bxc6 h6 21. Rc3 Nd6
{ Black gets a fantastic knight on d6. They will play Rc7-Rdc8 next. The bishop on c6 is more of an obligation, and as we have seen several times in endgames, the outside pawn majority is far more important than the central pawns. This position occurred in a 2020 correspondence game, and Black had a comfortable game. }
