1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 c5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. e4 Nxc3 7. bxc3 cxd4 8.
cxd4 Bb4+ 9. Bd2 Bxd2+ 10. Qxd2 O-O 11. Bb5
{ Provoking Black to play a6 and claiming the b6 square will get weaker. }
11... a6
{ Black accepts the challenge and goes on to prove that a6 is a useful move. }
12. Be2 b5
{ That's the way Black takes care of the weak b6 square :@@EndBracket@@ } 13.
O-O Bb7 14. Qe3 Nc6
{ This is a worse version for White compared to other lines that we have seen. Black got to expand on the queenside, and White didn't get anything obvious against it. }
