17. dxe6
{ Both  17.Qb2  and  17.Qf4  would be met by  17...Qf6  . Black would happily trade a few pieces. }
17... fxe6
{ If you are only looking at the pawn on e6 and frowning, then please also pay attention to the bishop on b7, the knight on c5, rook on f8, White's pawn on e4, and last but not the least, Black's queenside majority. }
18. Qb2 Qe7
{ Black gets a huge counter against White's minor pieces and the pawn on e4. The knight on c5 is super powerful, and White can do nothing about it. }
