15... h6
{ A lovely move order finesse. Black waits for White to show their plans.  If Black rushes with  15...Nf6  then after  16.d5  exd5  17.exd5  Re8  18.d6  gives White some pressure. Black is now claiming that White got everything they wanted, yet they can't strike. The move h6 is politely telling your opponent, 'I am not intimidated with your play. Please show me your plans'. Black also deliberately keeps the rook on f8, which protects the f7 pawn once the center blows up and/or White knight comes to e5 in the future. }
