17. Qh4
{ Keeping the queens on the board and trying for the central break d5 again.  17.Qg4  Nf6  allows the extra tempo to Black, so Qh4 seems the most natural square for White's queen. }
17... Rfe8 { The rook is nicely placed on e8, getting ready for d5 ideas. } 18.
h3
{ Difficult to give white some concrete suggestions here. Black is ready for d5 and playing g4 never works due to Qf4 ideas. }
18... b5
{ This is an additional option. Black could also play  18...Nf6  that would transpose into the 16.h3 line. Once Black has taken care of White's plans in the center and kingside, this queenside expansion with b5-a5-a4 is a very typical way of harassing the bishop on b3. }
19. d5
{ White decides to break. Once again, it is hard to find anything else at this stage. }
19... exd5 20. exd5 Rxe1+
{ Exchanging pieces! That is why the rook was waiting on e8. } 21. Rxe1 Nf6
