7. Na3 { White sacrifices a pawn and develops rapidly. } 7... cxd4 8. Nxc4 Bc5
{ Black is ready to castle and keeps his central pawn alive. It is not as trivial as it looks since White has ideas with a3-b4, b3-Bb2, etc. Though it is not as popular as other lines, it has been played by Carlsen, Caruana, Dubov, Gelfand, Leko, Shirov, etc. An entire chapter has covered this line, making sure that Black gets a comfortable position and the readers get complete clarity through move-by-move logical explanations. }
