1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 d5 4. Nf3 dxc4 5. Bg2
{ 5.Qa4  Nbd7  6.Bg2  and  6.Qxc4  a6  7.Bg2  is covered from  4. Bg2 move order.   5.Qc2  is weaker than 5.Qa4 as apart from allowing Black to transpose with  5...Nbd7  6.Qa4  .   White also allows an even stronger option after  5.Qc2  of  5...a6  when after  6.Qxc4  b5  Black gets the bishop to b7 and is ready to play Nbd7-c5 with no trouble whatsoever. }
5... c5 6. Qa4+
{ The last chance to give Qa4+ before Black plays Nc6. The point of this move is to meet  6...Nc6  with  7.Ne5  . }
6... Nbd7
{ Our response remains the same all of the time. We meet Qa4+ with Nbd7.  7.dxc5  Bxc5  8.Qxc4  a6  and  7.dxc5  Bxc5  8.O-O  a6  9.Qxc4  are covered from a different move order. }
7. O-O { 7.Qxc4  is covered from 4.Bg2 move order. } 7... a6 8. Nc3
{ The only independent move as both  8.Qxc4  and  8.dxc5  Bxc5  9.Qxc4  is covered in the mainline from the  4. Bg2 move order. }
8... Rb8 { Renewing the threat of b5. } 9. dxc5
{ 9.Qxc4  b5  10.Qd3  Bb7  11.dxc5  or  11.Bf4  Rc8  12.dxc5  will eventually transpose into 9.dxc5 line. }
9... Bxc5 10. Qxc4 b5
{ Black continues to play logically and makes room for the light-squared bishop on b7. }
11. Qd3
{ The most popular move in the position. White keeps the queen in the center to have more control over the d-file.  Trying to create an attack on the kingside with  11.Qh4  will not work when the bishop is on g2. The bishop needs to be on the other diagonal to create some threats on the kingside.  The queen alone will not suffice to scare Black and Black can just play  11...O-O  with a fine position. }
11... Bb7 { Just in time to meet Bf4 with Rc8. } 12. Bf4 Rc8
{ Black is now ready to castle and White cannot stop it. } 13. Rad1
{ 13.Ng5  Bxg2  14.Kxg2  O-O  looks fine for Black when White doesn't have a target, and Black has finished the development nicely.   13.Ne5  Bxg2  14.Kxg2  Nxe5  15.Qxd8  Rxd8  happened a few times when Black gets an easy endgame to play without having any weaknesses. The position remains balanced. }
13... O-O
{ White should act fast now. Otherwise, they can get into a worse position. Black wants to get Qb6-Rfd8 next. }
14. Ne5 { This is a wise decision to simplify the position. } 14... Bxg2 15.
Kxg2 Nxe5 16. Bxe5 Be7
{ Black is ready to get into an endgame where we have no weaknesses. } 17. Qf3
Qb6
{ Once again, Black gets a position with zero weaknesses and has nothing to worry about. }
