14. Bxa1 Nxb4 15. Ncxe5 O-O 16. Nd3
{ This was played in a correspondence game in 2016. After  16.Bxd4  b6  Black gets  Bb7  and has nothing to complain about from the opening. }
16... Nxd3 17. Qxd3 Re8
{ White will eventually get back the pawn on d4, but Black will keep the outside passed pawn, which will be safe on b6. The pawn on e2 remains a target. The position has been simplified a lot, and Black has nothing to worry about. }
