15... Rc8
{ It may look like things are very complex and all pieces are hanging, but ironically it is a very stable position as every single Black's piece are protected :@@EndBracket@@ }
16. Qxb4 { White has no other choice, but to simplify. } 16... Bxb4 17. Bxd7
Rxc1+ 18. Bxc1 Nxd7
{ Finally, the smoke has cleared, and after White managed to exchange all of the active pieces they are the ones who are underdeveloped now! The king on f8 is strong as it is ready to march in the center right away. Thanks to White's outside pawn majority, the engine calls it even but I would rather be Black here. 1/2-1/2 Leko,P @@StartBracket@@2734@@EndBracket@@-Kramnik,V @@StartBracket@@2790@@EndBracket@@ Dortmund 2010. }
