{ A new idea found around 2009 but was only played in 2018 when Wojtaszek @@StartBracket@@more commonly known as Radek@@EndBracket@@ used this idea to win a nice game against Adams. Radek contributed hugely to the entire Catalan repertoire for team Anand and had many interesting new ideas that we could use during and after the match.  This move which is very difficult to meet for the first time practically gave a lot of trouble to Adams. The idea is straightforward if we compare it with Leko - Kramnik started with  13.Qb3  Bxd6  14.Rc1  Qb4!  By sacrificing the pawn and gaining an extra a3 move, White stopped this Qb4 resource that was used by Kramnik. }
