13... Qb5 { Choice of Stockfish. This looks more dynamic to me. } 14. Qxd4 O-O
{ Now the pawn on e2 is attacked and Black also threatens to play Rfd8. } 15.
e3 Ng4
{ There is nothing wrong with 15... Rfd8 either, but this move is more concrete. Black attacks the bishop on e5 and is ready to give up the g7 pawn. }
16. Qxg4
