15. Qd2
{ White tries to enter with his queen to the kingside. In the online olympiad 2021 Bu had a game with Black when White opted for  15.d5  and after  15...exd5  16.Qxd5  Be6  17.Qh5  Qd5  , White was dead lost with no attack on the kingside, and Black's double bishop and strong pawns on the queenside sealed White's fate. }
15... f5 16. Nc5
{ After  16.Neg5  Bf6  , the computer evaluation of -2 is not exaggerating. White's pieces lack coordination, and there will be no way to match Black's double bishop and the pressure on the center and queenside. }
16... Be8
{ Our bishop will eventually get active so there is no point to give it up now. Moreover, the knight on c5 is now getting under attack. Engine tried to save in some bizarre way hoping for some kind of perpetual with  17.Nb7  Qc7  18.Qh6  but also says that Black should avoid that by playing f6 and remains better. This position occurred in the game 0-1 @@StartBracket@@42@@EndBracket@@ Al Sayed, M @@StartBracket@@2502@@EndBracket@@-Bu, X @@StartBracket@@2699@@EndBracket@@ Sharjah 2014 }
