8. Rxd1 Bxc5
{ For now, Black has an extra pawn. In order for White to win the pawn back, they must make some concessions. }
9. Nc3
{ The knight on c3 is not ideal, but White's argument here is that they avoided c3 for Black.   9.Bg5  makes no sense when Black can go  9...Ng4  and White won't be able to play  10.e3  due to  10...h6  when the bishop on g5 will end up trapped. }
9... Bd7
{ An important move. Black should not play in a naive way like  9...O-O  when after  10.Nd2  White will get exactly what they wanted.   By playing  9...Bd7  Black is ready to meet  10.Nd2  with  10...Na5  when White knight on c3 gets restricted by the bishop on d7. }
10. Bf4
{ Was played by Dubov once. White is focusing on rapid development and getting all his pieces out.  10.Bg5  can be answered, with  10...h6  when White will have to give up the bishop for a knight. }
