12. Nb5 { Attacking the pawn on c4. } 12... e5
{ The knight on b5 is loose, and Black takes advantage of that. } 13. Be3
{ 13.Nxe5  Nxe5  14.Bxe5  Bxb5  would lose a piece for White. } 13... Na5
{ Protecting the c4 pawn, getting ready for Bxc5 with Rxc5, and attacking the b5 knight. A multipurpose move. }
14. Nd6+ Bxd6 15. Rxd6 Ke7
{ We see the point of delaying castle. Anticipating an endgame, Black keeps the king in the center. }
16. Rdd1
{ Only move that is not -3 for White. After  16.Rd2  c3  Black gets the knight to c4 with tempo and completely crushes White. }
16... c3
{ White's pawn structure will get broken, or they can't take the pawn on c3. Either way, it is White who should think about equality here. }
