{ For now, Black has an extra pawn. In order for White to win the pawn back, they must make some concessions. }
9. Nfd2
{ This highly interesting move was first played at a GM level by Women World Champion Ju Wenjun in 2016. It soon became popular when Magnus used this move to beat Harikrishna in World Rapid 2017. White wants to take the pawn on c4 with the f3 knight so that the bishop on g2 remains open. }
