12. Bg5 { Planning to play Nfd4 next. } 12... e5
{ Not giving a second chance to White to put any of the knights on d4. Black is now ready to develop the light-squared bishop. }
13. Bxf6 gxf6
{ This is an instructive moment. Black is restricting the knights and keeping Ba3 ideas open. }
14. Nh4 Ba3
{ Not allowing White to push the queenside pawns and restricting the rook on a1. Be6 is coming next. }
15. Rab1 Be6
{ With clear weaknesses on the queenside and having zero compensation against the pair of bishops, White has some issues here to solve. }
