[White "Chapter 27: dxc5 Endgame (9.Nbd2-11.Nb3 Be7 12.c4)"]
[Black "dxc5 endgame 9.Nbd2 -11.Nb3 Be7 12.c4 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 dxc4 5. Bg2 c5 6. O-O Nc6 7. dxc5 Qxd1 8.
Rxd1 Bxc5 9. Nbd2 c3 10. bxc3 O-O 11. Nb3 Be7 12. c4
{ This is the second most popular move after  12.Nfd4  . White keeps their plans flexible. They can now develop the bishop on e3/f4/b2 or play a4-a5 or go for c5. Primarily, for now, they stopped Black from getting Nd5 ideas. }
12... Bd7
{ Black also has various plans at their disposal. Depending on how White develops Black will decide on their plans. Black's plans are as follows: Rac8-Rfd8-Be8 ideas, Rfc8-Be8-Nd8 ideas, playing b6 and restricting the knight on b3, playing e5, and taking the d4 square from White's knights.  Let us understand the position clearly. White's pieces have more free space, but Black has a better pawn structure. So, White's nature of advantage is dynamic while Black's advantage is static. That means if Black can finish the development and White doesn't take any action, then Black might even take over. }
13. Nfd4
{ This move was played a few times but doesn't make a strong impression. White's main idea is to claim that Black is missing Nd5 plans. For instance, in the mainline 12.Nfd4, we are taking on d4 and going Nd5. Here we can't do that. }
13... Rac8
{ Taking advantage of the c4-Bd7 move inclusion. Black had ample time to take care of the queenside and finish development. }
14. Nb5
{ White now tries to occupy the d6 square and get a bishop-pair advantage. }
14... Ne5
{ Now that Black finished development, we charge on White's weak spot on c4. }
15. Bxb7 Rb8
{ Black would like to put the knight on c4 instead of the rook obviously. } 16.
Bf4
{ If White would have moved the b7 bishop, then Black takes Nxc4, and we have zero issues in the position. }
16... Nxc4 17. Bxb8 Rxb8
{ Black gets back the material, and White has zero targets. Black had no problems in the game ½-½ Adly,A @@StartBracket@@2626@@EndBracket@@ -Praggnanandhaa,R @@StartBracket@@2530@@EndBracket@@ Sitges 2018 }
