{ 14.a4  b6  15.Bb2  f5  transposes to 14.Bb2 line that we will be seeing now. 14.a4 was the actual move order for Jumabaev - Caruana,  World Cup 2021 }
14... f5
{ The whole point of this line. Block the bishop on g2: for that, we need to stabilize the knight on d5. Hence we stop White from playing e4. Next, we want to restrict the knight on b3 by going b6. No need to do anything against the bishop on b2 as it is self restricted :@@EndBracket@@ }
15. Na5
{ Was played in the game Wei, Y @@StartBracket@@2736@@EndBracket@@ -So, W @@StartBracket@@2754@@EndBracket@@ Abidjan 2019 }
15... Bd7
{ I like this more than b6 that happened in the game. Black threatens b6 and takes advantage of the unprotected bishop on b2. It is because of this bishop White is unable to take on b7 due to Rb8. }
16. Rdc1 Rfc8
{ Finally, nothing can stop Black from chasing the knight away with b6. White can get the knight to e5 via c4, but this doesn't bother Black as he will keep his bishop e8.   Both White's bishops will be bad, and Black will be ready to push forward the queenside pawns. }
