{ This position occurred twice and in both games, Black missed a fine prophylaxis. }
16... Re8
{ Black would love to play Bd7, but after Bxd5-exd5-Rc7, Black can't move his bishop from d7 as the bishop on e7 hangs. Hence 16...Re8! }
17. Bf4 Bd7 18. Bxd5 exd5 19. Rc7 Bb5
{ The point of 16...Re8 becomes clear. The bishop on e7 remains protected. The pawn on e2 hangs, and Black is ready to chase away White's rook from c7 by going Bd8. The knight on b3 is still inactive. Black gets the initiative here. }
