[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Training Positions"]
[Black "Position #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. g3 d5 3. Bg2 { 3.Nf3  c5  4.Bg2  transposes to the mainline. }
3... c5 4. Nf3 cxd4 5. O-O h6
{ An excellent prophylactic move. Black does not commit with Nc6 to make sure after Nxd4, he can play e5, and White won't have Nxc6. Black also made sure not to play e6 so that he plays e5 at one go, saving a tempo. Realizing that he will get full control over the center, black makes sure that the center is consolidated. This he does by playing h6! Chess is beautiful, isn't it? The move h6 tells the d5 pawn that I have got your back. The d5 pawn will be protected by the knight on f6, and the knight gets immunity from Bg5 thanks to h6 :@@EndBracket@@ }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
