{ A very easy move to miss. It has never occurred in tournament practice yet. This highly anti-positional move wins immediately for Black tactically. }
10. Bxf3
{ There was no other good way to take the bishop. White is strategically clearly better now, but the next move spoils the fun for White. }
10... Qc7
{ There is no way to save the pawn on c2 for White. They can't move the c-pawn due to the Nd3 fork while Rc1 runs into Nxa2. Black wins a pawn and gets a winning position. }
