1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 c5 5. Bg5 cxd4 6. Qxd4 Nc6 7. Bxf6 gxf6
{ We should try and keep the queens on the board. Breaking the pawn structure is fine as well since Black has the bishop pair and better central control. }
8. Qh4 dxc4
{ Opening up the game completely, taking full advantage of having a pair of bishops. }
9. Rd1
{ After  9.Qxc4  Qb6  , it would be difficult to cope with Black's threats. By playing  9. Rd1 White takes advantage of the queen placement on h4 that stops Black from playing Qb6 as the f6 pawn hangs. }
9... Bd7 10. e3
{ 10.e4  b5  11.Nxb5  Rb8  would be annoying for White as they are missing Qxc4 ideas and  12.Bxc4  Rxb5  13.Bxb5  Qa5  loses material. }
10... f5
{ Now Black is ready to trade queens and get the bishop to g7. The engine gives a slight edge to Black already. }
