exd4 Be7 9. O-O O-O 10. Bxd5 exd5 11. Qb3 Bg4
{ There are other moves also, but this looks cleanest. Black targets the knight on f3. }
12. Nxd5
{ After  12.Qxb7  Nb4  Black gives the double threat of Rb8-Ra8 and Bxf3 that gives us ample compensation. }
12... Bd6
{ Be6 would win a piece now if White doesn't take care of the threat. } 13. Bg5
