1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 c5 5. e3 Nc6 6. cxd5 Nxd5 7. Bd3 Be7 8. O-O
O-O 9. Nxd5 Qxd5 10. e4 Qd7
{ A lovely trick. Black keeps the d8 square available for the rook. } 11. dxc5
{ 11.d5  Rd8  also gives White a tough position due to the pin on the d-file. }
11... Rd8 { This was the point of keeping the d8 square free. } 12. Be2
{ 12.Bc2  also leads to a similar position after the queen trade. } 12... Qxd1
13. Rxd1 Rxd1+ 14. Bxd1 Bxc5
{ Black has nothing to complain about in this endgame where we don't have any weaknesses. In fact, the engines are slightly tilted towards Black. }
