O-O 9. a3 cxd4 10. exd4 Bf6 11. Be4 Nce7 12. h4 Bd7 13. Ng5
{ After  13.h5  Bc6  , it is difficult to deal with the Nxc3 threats, and Black creates play faster in the center. The computer already gives a substantial advantage for Black. It is nice to note that after a long think, the engine feels the best way for White here to play is  13.Qd3  h6  14.Bh7+  Kh8  15.Be4  :-@@EndBracket@@ Obviously, if Black wants, they can repeat with  15...Kg8  . }
13... g6
{ White pushed too far artificially, and Black already took over. The attack here is nothing but an illusion. }
14. Nf3
{ Realizing there is no attack, White comes back to f3, admitting that the entire strategy has backfired and is now looking for equality. }
14... Bc6
{ Black got complete control in the center while White doesn't have any attack on any side of the board. Black threatens to take on c3 and exchange a few more pieces so that White's weak pawn structure becomes more prominent. Black was better in the game 1/2-1/2 @@StartBracket@@45@@EndBracket@@ Giri,A @@StartBracket@@2764@@EndBracket@@ -Shankland,S @@StartBracket@@2691@@EndBracket@@ chess24.com INT 2021. }
