cxd4 Bb4+ 9. Bd2 Bxd2+ 10. Qxd2 O-O 11. Be2 b6 12. O-O Bb7 13. Qe3 Nc6 14. Rad1
Rc8 15. d5 exd5 16. exd5 Nb4 17. d6 Nd5
{ The most natural move. Blocking the d-file, attacking the queen, attacking the d6 pawn, and threatening Nc3 as well. How many more reasons do we need to play this move? In the game, shockingly Black, played the reckless  17...Nxa2  and was immediately lost once White played  18.d7  . }
18. Qa3
{ Only way to keep the pawn alive since  18.Qe5  was losing to  18...Re8  . }
18... Nc3 { The knight starts showing its strength. } 19. Rd2 Rc5
{ White has no way to save the pawn, and the position becomes dead lost. } *

