cxd4 Bb4+ 9. Bd2 Bxd2+ 10. Qxd2 O-O 11. Bd3 Nc6 12. e5 Ne7
{ I am also equally surprised to see that only two games out of more than 30 games that reached this position continued in this manner. The most popular move by Black here is  12...Qa5  , which is a strategic mistake. We should wait for White to castle before trading the queens. The move  12...Ne7  seems most logical. Black is getting ready to bring the bishop out and eventually take control of the d5-square. }
13. O-O Bd7
{ White got themselves into a strategically worse position with the weak pawn on d4. Black will put pressure on it with Bc6 next. White has to be very creative now to get an equal position. }
