20. Rc1 Qb5
{ Another only move!  20...Rxd2  21.Rxc5  wins for White when they have back rank under control, and the d2 rook is under attack. Finally, we have reached the position which solves the mystery of pawn being on a7 and  @@StartFEN@@r5k1/1p3ppp/p3R3/1q1r4/8/5N2/P2Q1PPP/2R3K1 w - - 2 21@@EndFEN@@ a6. With the pawn on a6, White would be winning here with  21.Rb6!!  This is the reason why I prefer 12...Bd7 over 12...Qe7. There is no headache to remember when it works and when it doesn't :@@EndBracket@@ }
21. Qe1
{ 21.Qe2  or  21.Qe3  will reach the same position after  21...fxe6  . } 21...
fxe6 22. Qxe6+ { The sequence of forced moves continues... } 22... Kh8 23. Ng5
{ Once again the only move to escape with a draw. } 23... Qd7
{ The smoke has cleared, and White will have to give perpetual. } 24. Nf7+ Kg8
25. Nh6+ Kh8
