Rac8 15. Bb3 Qa3 16. d5 exd5 17. exd5 Na5
{ It turns out Black can simply sacrifice the pawn! } 18. Qxa7 Qc5
{ A fantastic strategic move. Despite being a pawn down, Black wants to get to an endgame. }
19. Qxc5 { Forced. } 19... Rxc5
{ Black goes for the central pawn. It turns out this pawn on d5 is falling by force. The black king is way too close to it. }
20. Rfd1
{ After  20.d6  Nxb3  21.axb3  Rd8  Black goes Bc6-Rb5-Kf8, and White eventually loses the extra pawn. Engine evaluation of 0.00 seems fair. }
20... Bg4 21. d6 Rd8
{ No, we are not begging for a draw. We are simply going to gobble the pawn on d6. }
22. Rd4 Bxf3 23. gxf3 Nxb3 24. axb3 Rc6
{ The king will come to the e-file. White will have to give perpetual not to get into an uncomfortable position. The game ends in a draw now. }
