Rad1 Rc8 15. Bb3 h6 16. Re3 Nf6 17. Qe1 Re8 18. h3 Qc7 19. d5 exd5 20. e5 Nd7
21. Ba4 Bc6 22. Bc2 Nf8 23. Nd4 Ne6 24. Nf5 d4
{ This is the right moment to strike with d4. Now the position becomes extremely wild, and both sides will be playing with fire. }
25. Rg3
{ The most human move, going for an attack on the kingside. After  25.Nxd4  Black can either play:  The solid  25...Nxd4  26.Rxd4  Bd5  with a balanced position when the c2 bishop is under attack.   - Or they can choose the dynamic  25.Nxd4  25...Bxg2  26.Nxe6  fxe6  27.Bg6  Bd5  when the bishop on d5 becomes a gigantic monster after  28.Bxe8  Rxe8  Black gets huge compensation. I would go for the second option :@@EndBracket@@ }
25... Bxg2
{ Showing zero respect towards White's attack! Black has their own plans of attacking the kingside :@@EndBracket@@ }
26. Bb3
{ After the automatic  26.Nxh6  Kf8  White gets into huge trouble with both minor pieces hanging. }
26... Ba8
{ The bishop has done its job and exposed White's king. Now it is time to come back and keep attacking from the long diagonal. }
27. Nxh6+ Kf8 28. Nf5 { Only move that doesn't lose instantly. } 28... Qc5
{ We are ready to meet Nd6 with Nf4 now } *

