Nf6 15. Bd3 h6 16. a5 a6 17. axb6 Qxb6 18. Rab1 Qc7 19. g4 a5
{ A very practical move. There is no need to stop White's kingside advance. They are also weakening their king. According to the engines, Black is also fine after  19...Nxg4  20.Rec1  Qe7  21.Qf4  f5!  22.Rc7  fxe4  23.Rxe7  Rxf4  24.Rbxb7  exd3  , and it ends with some perpetual. I'm not particularly eager to allow White's rooks on the seventh rank, and in general, I would like to keep winning chances here from Black. Playing a5 is much easier than we did for 18.g4 lines. }
20. g5
{ White cannot play  20.h4  as after  20...Nxg4  the knight on g4, gets complete stability. After  21.Rec1  Qb8  22.e5  Ra7  there is no way to get rid of the knight from g4, and Black is close to winning. }
