cxd4 Bb4+ 9. Bd2 Bxd2+ 10. Qxd2 O-O 11. Bc4 Nd7 12. O-O b6 13. Rfe1 Bb7 14.
Rad1 Rc8 15. Bb3 h6 16. h3 Nf6 17. d5 exd5 18. Qf4 Rc5
{ Stopping one threat. Now after  19.exd5  Bxd5  Black remains one pawn up with a clear better position. }
19. e5
{ White plays e5 when Black cannot play Ne4 due to the pin on the d-file, and playing Nd7 makes no sense, as the e5 pawn is well protected, and White continues Nd4-Nf5. }
19... Ne8
{ A fantastic resource. Black reroutes the knight to e6 via c7 to combat White's knight that will come to d4. }
20. Nd4
{ The best way to get to f5. After  20.Nh4  Qg5!  Black forces a queen trade.   20.Nd4  Qg5  would be a mistake when White has the brilliant  21.Qh2  with the idea of f4 and the knight on d4 is not hanging, unlike the 20.Nh4 variation. }
20... Nc7 { Black prepares Qg5 and Ne6 ideas. } 21. Qe3
{ 21.Nf5  Qg5  brings nothing for White, so they get ready to meet Qg5 now with f4. }
21... Ne6
{ Getting rid of the knight on d4.  22.Nf5  Qg5  works as White is missing f4 ideas. }
22. f4
{ White stops Qg5 and takes space in the kingside, but now their strongest piece is gone. }
22... Nxd4
{ Of course Black would love to eliminate the strong knight on d4. They now remain one pawn up. }
23. Rxd4 Qd7
{ It is difficult for White to continue the attack. They are not getting f5 easily after  24.Qf2  , a fantastic strategic move would be to play  24...Qf5  , when the only way to get rid of the queen will be to play g4 @@StartBracket@@White is never getting Bc2 as Black plays Rfc8 next@@EndBracket@@, and once g4 is played, Black comes back with the queen, and now it is impossible to put pressure on the g7 pawn @@StartBracket@@thanks to White's pawn on g4@@EndBracket@@. Black then triples on the c-file and pushes the queenside pawns with b5-a5-a4.   In a correspondence game 2020, White could not find anything better than  24.Kh2  and played slowly. Black continued with  24...Rfc8  , and had no problem in the entire game. 1/2-1/2 Denisov, T @@StartBracket@@2210@@EndBracket@@-Sorcinelli, A @@StartBracket@@2303@@EndBracket@@ LSS email 2020. }
