1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 d5 4. Bg2 dxc4 5. Qa4+ Nbd7 6. Qxc4 c5
{ It is crucial to avoid any move order trick by White. After the natural  7...a6  Fabiano used a very interesting idea of going  8.Be3  b5  9.Qc1  against Anand in the 2018 Olympiad. Later he developed the knight from h3 instead of f3 to keep the bishop on g2 open.   By playing,  7...c5  Black avoids those ideas and practically forces White to develop his knight on f3 next. }
