19. Qxb4 Nd5 20. Qd2 Nxe3
{ And white cannot retake the knight so easily, c3 comes fast. } 21. fxe3
{ Unfortunate but forced. After  21.Qxe3  c3  22.bxc3  Qa5  Black wins on the spot due to the material advantage.   After  21.Rxe3  Ba4  , there is no way to get back the knight on  a1  so easily. }
21... c3 { Forcing White to take on c3 } 22. bxc3 Qe7
{ By attacking the knight on a3, Black saves his own knight on a1. } 23. Rxa1
Qxa3 24. Qxd7 Rxc3
{ Every single engine gives 0.00, and in a 2018 correspondence game, it ended in a draw soon. White is about to lose the pawn on e3, and the pawn on a2 makes the a1 rook passive. White's king is not safe, which fully compensates for the material imbalance. ½-½ Ostriker,J @@StartBracket@@2561@@EndBracket@@ -Dothan,Y @@StartBracket@@2538@@EndBracket@@ ICCF email 2018 }
