{ An important move. White would love to take on d5 once Black plays a5. Black would rather wait for White to move the knight from b4 and only then think about fixing the a4 pawn by going a5. Black gives a positional threat of taking the knight on b4 and exchanging the light-squared bishop. We want to exchange all of the active pieces for White and leave them with the bad dark-squared bishop. }
